---
import SiteLayout from '../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';

const locale = 'en';
---

<SiteLayout title="Methodology" description="Realpha Blog's six-gate validation process: bias controls, baselines, trading costs, significance correction, and cross-model red-team review." locale={locale} path="/en/methodology/" alternatePath="/methodology/" breadcrumbs={[{ name: 'Methodology', path: '/en/methodology/' }]}>
	<main class="page article-shell">
		<header class="article-header">
			<h1 class="article-title">Methodology</h1>
			<p class="lead">The validation gates every research conclusion must pass before it appears here.</p>
		</header>
		<div class="prose">
			<p>Every conclusion on this site goes through the same process: ① the dataset includes delisted stocks to handle survivorship bias; ② signal calculations use only information available at that point in time to prevent look-ahead bias; ③ results are compared with a naive buy-anything baseline and split by price band to prevent low-priced-stock inflation; ④ net returns are checked after trading costs; ⑤ overlapping holding periods use Newey-West correction for statistical significance; ⑥ major conclusions are handed to AI models from different companies for red-team review. Results that fail the six gates are labeled as negative results and published honestly.</p>
			<figure class="method-flow">
				<svg class="flow-svg" viewBox="0 0 720 720" role="img" aria-labelledby="method-flow-title method-flow-desc">
					<title id="method-flow-title">Six-step validation flow</title>
					<desc id="method-flow-desc">A linear flow covering data, signals, baselines, costs, significance, and cross-model red-team review.</desc>
					<line x1="78" y1="82" x2="78" y2="598" stroke="var(--accent)" stroke-width="4" stroke-linecap="round"></line>
					{[
						['1', 'Include delisted stocks', 'Control survivorship bias', 72],
						['2', 'Use only then-known data', 'Prevent look-ahead bias', 176],
						['3', 'Baseline and price bands', 'Control low-price inflation', 280],
						['4', 'Subtract trading costs', 'Check net return', 384],
						['5', 'Newey-West correction', 'Handle overlapping holds', 488],
						['6', 'Cross-model red team', 'Challenge major claims', 592],
					].map(([number, title, note, y]) => (
						<g>
							<circle cx="78" cy={y} r="28" fill="var(--paper)" stroke="var(--accent)" stroke-width="4"></circle>
							<text x="78" y={Number(y) + 7} text-anchor="middle" font-size="22">{number}</text>
							<rect x="130" y={Number(y) - 36} width="510" height="72" rx="10" fill="var(--paper)" stroke="var(--line)"></rect>
							<text x="158" y={Number(y) - 6} font-size="21">{title}</text>
							<text class="flow-note" x="158" y={Number(y) + 23} font-size="16">{note}</text>
						</g>
					))}
				</svg>
			</figure>
		</div>
	</main>
</SiteLayout>
